  "body": "#### Current behavior\r\n- Display and Language settings are per account and can only be changed after account creation/import and login\r\n- When Display and Language settings are changed, these changes are not visible on the login screen\r\n\r\n#### Proposed behavior\r\n- ~Account creation: Support 'default app mode' on Windows (and equivalent on Mac and Linux) and set appearance mode on first time launch to 'System' as default~ moved to #2177 \r\n- Login screen: Add option to change global Display and Language setting on the login screen (https://i.imgur.com/FQZMMcG.png)\r\n- Settings: Keep option to change global Display and Language setting in Settings post login\r\n- Additional account creation: When a new account is created, the global setting is applied\r\n\r\n**********\r\n#### User stories\r\n- User story 1\r\n     - As a user _who opted to change the display setting,_\r\n     - I want _this setting to apply to my most frequently visited screens_\r\n     - Because _that's why I chose the setting_\r\n\r\n- User story 2 --> addressed by #2177 \r\n     - As a user _who is new to Status_\r\n     - I want _for the application to respect my system Language and Display settings on launch (account creation/import)_\r\n     - Because _these are settings I prefer for my applications_\r\n     \r\n## Notes\r\nA 3rd user stories is not covered by this solution as it has conflicting requirements\r\n- User story 3\r\n     - As a user _who has multiple accounts,_ \r\n     - I want _to set a language for each_ \r\n     - So that _I can switch between languages_\r\n\r\nI suspect changing these might be different issues:\r\n- Listen to dark mode system setting on windows, mac, Linux\r\n- Change toolbar to respect appearance setting\r\n- Hide Language on login screen when only one language (EN) is available\r\n",
